news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation eyes private land at Bakery Junction for housing scheme
news.para: The project was launched in 2020; however the work could not be started as the beneficiaries have disagreed with the authorities regarding transit accommodation.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes structures in illegal colonies
news.para: According to senior IMC officials, one Chetan Bhumiya was allegedly developing an illegal colony by the name of Lunia compound in around four acres of land situated on AB Road under Lasudia police station.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body demolishes illegal constructions
news.para: The town planning and estate management department teams demolished 2,959 sq feet of illegal construction from TP scheme 30 in Meghaninagar and 1,500 sq feet from 10 commercial units located in TP scheme 33 in Chandlodia.

news.title: J&K admin transfers land for construction of housing colonies in Srinagar, Budgam
news.para: The approval for transfer of land measuring over 289 acres in seven villages at 17 locations in Srinagar and Budgam districts, free of cost in favour of HUDD for construction of housing colonies, was accorded by the Administrative Council (AC).

news.title: NDMC, EDMC extend last date for payment of property tax with amnesty scheme
news.para: Standing Committee Chairman of the North Delhi Municipal Corporation Jogi Ram Jain said the NDMC has extended the last date for the first phase of tax amnesty scheme from January 31 to February 15.

news.title: Small homes, plots in Hyderabad to feel the heat of price revision: Experts
news.para: ​It is also expected to impact those eying plots in Hyderabad’s peripheral areas – Shankarpally, Ghatkesar, Medcal among others – where the rates have shot up anywhere between 30% and 40%.

news.title: Kolkata: HIDCO plans to set up vertical city in New Town
news.para: However, the authorities have not specified the number of floors that the proposed building will have. The agency that will be selected to construct the building will have to complete the project in two years from the day the work commences.

news.title: Launch all housing works by March 31: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: He told them to focus on resolving court cases and assist the beneficiaries in availing bank loans for their houses and instructed the collectors, JCs and municipal commissioners to conduct periodical inspections.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit rises 7% to Rs 7.68 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income of the company rose to Rs 226.88 crore in the quarter, from Rs 184.86 crore in year-ago period. Total expenses also increased to Rs 216.93 crore, as against Rs 175.23 crore earlier.

news.title: Amitabh Bachchan sells Gulmohar Park family home 'Sopaan' for Rs 23 crore
news.para: The property has been bought by Avni Bader, CEO of Nezone group of companies, who lives close by and has known the Bachchan family for more than 35 years.

news.title: Fifty owners who flouted building rules in Gurugram's DLF-3 will be booked: DTCP
news.para: These 50 properties are in S, U and V blocks of the colony. The DTCP has now sent a list of these buildings to the DLF 3 police station, seeking FIRs against the owners.

news.title: ED arrests businessman in Mumbai 'chawl' re-development money laundering case
news.para: Pravin Raut, a former director of a company called Guru Ashish Construction Pvt Ltd, was arrested following his questioning at the ED office in Mumbai.

news.title: Greece cuts property tax to help households hit by surging inflation
news.para: The measure follows a 2% increase in the minimum wage announced last month to help low-income earners tackle higher prices in energy bills and consumers goods.

news.title: Central Vista: Rs 2,600 crore for construction of non-residential office buildings
news.para: A sum of Rs 2,600.99 has been been allocated for the construction of non-residential office buildings, including the Parliament and Supreme Court of India. For residential purposes, the ministry has been given Rs 873.02 crore.

news.title: By building houses for poor, made them lakhpatis, women 'malkins': PM
news.para: In this year's budget, it has been stated that 80 lakh 'pucca' houses will be built for the poor and on this about Rs 48,000 crore will be spent, Modi said noting that this was also a way to bring people out of poverty.
